The Senior Urban Planner (Design & Project Management) is responsible for leading and supporting the design and project coordination of large-scale urban and master planning projects. The role involves close collaboration with internal teams, international consultants, and clients, from concept development through implementation.
Key Responsibilities
- Develop innovative urban and architectural design concepts, balancing creativity, functionality, and practical constraints;
- Translate complex ideas into clear, coherent design strategies that respond to spatial and contextual requirements;
- Act as the main point of contact for international clients and consultants, ensuring effective communication and project alignment;
- Contribute to design development from concept through detailed design and implementation stages;
- Prepare and support design presentations across all project phases, including graphics, 3D models, renderings, and technical details;
- Work closely with planning leadership to deliver team vision while managing day-to-day responsibilities independently;
- Handle internal and external communication and correspondence professionally;
- Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams across Vietnam and overseas offices as required;
- Support project coordination for large-scale, multi-disciplinary projects involving multiple stakeholders and locations;
Demonstrate awareness of global urban design trends, standards, and emerging issues;
- Work proactively within a multi-skilled environment, coordinating with architects, planners, consultants, authorities, and developers;
- Ensure compliance with planning policies, guidelines, and project requirements.

